Given the database schema,
we can define several endpoints for the corresponding API: 1.Users API - `GET /api/users/`: Returns a list of all users.- `POST /api/users/`: Creates a new user.- `GET /api/users/{userId}/`: Returns details of a specific user.- `PUT /api/users/{userId}/`: Updates details of a specific user.- `DELETE /api/users/{userId}/`: Deletes a specific user.- `GET /api/users/{userId}/groups/`: Returns a list of groups the user belongs to.- `GET /api/users/{userId}/permissions/`: Returns a list of permissions the user has.2.Groups API - `GET /api/groups/`: Returns a list of all groups.- `POST /api/groups/`: Creates a new group.- `GET /api/groups/{groupId}/`: Returns details of a specific group.- `PUT /api/groups/{groupId}/`: Updates details of a specific group.- `DELETE /api/groups/{groupId}/`: Deletes a specific group.- `GET /api/groups/{groupId}/permissions/`: Returns a list of permissions associated with the group.3.Permissions API - `GET /api/permissions/`: Returns a list of all permissions.- `POST /api/permissions/`: Creates a new permission.- `GET /api/permissions/{permissionId}/`: Returns details of a specific permission.- `PUT /api/permissions/{permissionId}/`: Updates details of a specific permission.- `DELETE /api/permissions/{permissionId}/`: Deletes a specific permission.4.Badges API - `GET /api/badges/`: Returns a list of all badges.- `POST /api/badges/`: Creates a new badge.- `GET /api/badges/{badgeId}/`: Returns details of a specific badge.- `PUT /api/badges/{badgeId}/`: Updates details of a specific badge.- `DELETE /api/badges/{badgeId}/`: Deletes a specific badge.- `GET /api/badges/{badgeId}/users/`: Returns a list of users who have this badge.5.Boosters API - `GET /api/boosters/`: Returns a list of all boosters.- `POST /api/boosters/`: Creates a new booster.- `GET /api/boosters/{boosterId}/`: Returns details of a specific booster.- `PUT /api/boosters/{boosterId}/`: Updates details of a specific booster.- `DELETE /api/boosters/{boosterId}/`: Deletes a specific booster.- `GET /api/boosters/{boosterId}/users/`: Returns a list of users who have this booster.6.Verification
and Password Reset API - `POST /api/verify-email/`: Creates a new email verification token.- `POST /api/verify-email/{token}/`: Verifies the user 's email with the given token.
    - `POST /api/reset-password/`: Creates a new password reset token.
    - `POST /api/reset-password/{token}/`: Resets the user' s password with the given token.Please note that you may also want to consider authorization
and security measures like JWT authentication to restrict access to these endpoints depending on user roles
and permissions.